div.p:
Jeſus ſitting over againſt the Treaſury took notice of thoſe that caſt their Gifts into it;
Mark 12.41-44. Luke 21.1-4. 
and ſeeing a certain poor Widow caſting in two Mites, (which make a Farthing of our Mony) he called unto his Diſciples, and ſaid unto them, That this poor Widow hath given more, then all the Rest; becauſe theſe Rich Men, who have put much into the Treaſury, have given out of their abundance; but this Woman on the contrary hath out of her want given all ſhe had, even all her Living.
